commit.message:
Move generated ebuilds to EAPI=8

This PR changes the generated ebuilds to use DIST_ variables rather than MODULE_*.

Also, changes compatibility of generated ebuilds to EAPI=8, and updates
the copyright line in the generated files

Bug: https://bugs.gentoo.org/819513
Closes: https://github.com/gentoo-perl/g-cpan/pull/50
add test to check syntax, presence of 'use strict' & 'use warnings'
Release v0.17.0

add handling of 'repo_name:profile_rel_path' syntax in parent file

(close #42)
fix internal caching of repos, it depends on eroot value
add more tests with test data for EPREFIX kind of tests
place EROOT detecting in new, improve it and add more tests

add detection of EPREFIX and build of EROOT based on it

close github #47

add new gentoo repo path to possible values

and set tests plan explicitly
fix tests plan for non-developer running

drop old perl versions from travis config

since they were dropped from gentoo repo
fix POD code formatting

add 5.30 to list of perl versions (#27)

it is now available in the "portage"

migrate to ExtUtils::Manifest from Test::CheckManifest to test MANIFEST

due to issues in Test::CheckManifest
 https://github.com/reneeb/Test-CheckManifest/issues/20

update list of perl versions to modern (#27)

that are now available in the "portage"
update TODO, add task about EROOT detection
hotfix to avoid 'use of uninitialized value' (introduced by 505877ca)
fix warning in POD about EROOT
add warning if "GCPAN_OVERLAY" is not present in overlays/repos list

generate list of overlays only once and re-use it later in all places

so we sure what we have the same list
update POD to cover repos also in addition to overlays
remove unused var
add debug output for portage env

change to dump all passed args (@_) instead of first arg only ($_[0])

its allow to pass any structure to dump, like $gcpan_run->debug($env)

rename 'DEBUG' to 'debug' all over

so we keep one name/property ('debug') everywhere

simplify new(), add POD for it

also hide DEBUG arg in POD since it not for public usage

fix log output, now a log message appears in log file

post-fix after 9fd65004

Merge branch 'refactor/gentoo_cpan' into upstream_master

* refactor/gentoo_cpan:
  fix POD for transformCPAN() and tweak it a little
  add tests for transformCPAN()
  cleanup new() from all unnecessary stuff, now it's a tiny one
  refactor: use separate var for access to CPAN dist info
  rename test and update it to manage Gentoo::CPAN instead of Gentoo
fix POD for transformCPAN() and tweak it a little
add tests for transformCPAN()
